States Air Force  Captain Carico entered active duty through Air Force ROTC at the James Madison University in 2006  During her career she held a various positions  She is a core Space Officer and has worked as a Satellite Vehicle Operator for the MILSTAR constellation in 4th Space Operations Squadron  Schriever AFB  CO  Capt Carico has been a trainer and operator in the space cell of the 609th Air and Space Operations Center at Shaw AFB  SC and Al Udied Air Base in Qatar  She has also been a crew commander  flight commander and evaluator for SBIRS HEO Satellites in the 11th Space Warning Squadron  Schriever AFB  CO  EDUCATION 2006 Bachelor of Science degree in Kinesiology  James Madison University  VA 2006 Air and Space Basic Training  Maxwell AFB  AL 2010 Master of Health Science in Health Education  TUI University  CA 2012 Squadron Officer School  Maxwell AFB  AL 2014 Space 200  Peterson AFB  CO ASSIGNMENTS 1  June 2006   Aug 2006  Student  Air University  Maxwell AFB  AL 2  Aug 2006   April 2007  Student  533rd Training Squadron  Vandenberg AFB  CA 3  April 2007   Jan 2011  Crew Support Section Commander  4th Space Operations Squadron  Schriever AFB  CO 4  Jul 2010   Dec 2010  COD Space Flight Commander  609th Air and Space Operation Center  Shaw AFB  SC 5  Feb 2011  Mar 2013  Support Flight Commander  11th Space Warning Squadron  Schriever AFB  CO 12  Mar 2013   Present  Education Flight Commander  AFROTC Detachment 880  Virginia Military Institute  Lexington  VA MAJOR AWARDS AND DECORATIONS Air Force Commendation Medal Air Force Achievement Medal National Defense Service Medal Global War on Terrorism Service Medal EFFECTIVE DATES OF PROMOTION  Second Lieutenant May 31  2006 First Lieutenant May 31  2008 Captain May 31  2010  Current as of February 2015  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY Th